CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1953, pg. 23, reads: "HURRICANE - Pittsburghers and out-of-towners alike flocked to the grand opening Monday of the new Hurricane Club at 1603 Centre Avenue. This Exquisite addition to Pittsburgh's night spots lays claim to being one of the most modern restaurant - bars for many miles around...In the bottom left photo, left to right, are Thomas Smith, doorman, and Clifford Page, Lester Wilson, Frank Johnson and 'Jap' Washington, bartenders... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of men, from left: doorman Thomas "Smitty" Smith, and bartenders Clifford Page, Lester Wilson, Frank Johnson, and Jasper "Jap" Washington standing behind bar for Hurricane Club opening
